properties.place_name: Trail Ridge Road, Rocky Mountain National Park
properties.description: The Trail Ridge Road bisects the alpine country of Rocky Mountain National Park's higher elevations. The effects of a trip along Trail Ridge Road are dramatic, with steep increases in elevation and breathtaking vistas of deep canyons and jagged ridges. The peak height on the road is around 4,000 meters.
